    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Heater Controls</title>
        <para>The heater controls for the RE bus are located in two locations. The main heater controls are cable
            operated, and located under the right wing switch panel (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f47005152">Fig. 152, Item B</hotlnk>).
        </para>
        <para>The auxiliary heater controls for the bus body are located in the left wing switch panel (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f47005152">Fig. 152, Item A</hotlnk>).
        </para>
        <figure id="f47005152" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic id="g47005152.webp" filename="../figg47/g47005152.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="352px"
                     scalefitheight="352px"/>
            <caption>Figure 152. Heater Controls - A. Driver Left Wing Switch Panel and B. Main Heater Control Panel
                (Right Side)
            </caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">SWITCH PANEL MOUNTING SCREWS</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">INDICATOR LIGHT</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">DEFROST / BI-LEVEL / DRIVER STEPWELL CONTROL</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">RECIRCULATION CONTROL</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">HEATER CONTROL LEVER</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">HEATER FAN SPEED CONTROL SWITCH</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">DRIVER HEATER SWITCH</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">MID SHIP HEATER SWITCHES</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">BOOSTER PUMP SWITCH</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">REAR HEATER SWITCHES</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To access the right wing heater controls, locate the four mounting screws.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen and remove the mounting screws.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the panel front face.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcsubproc>
